Biography
 
Celrond was created on Xegony after a college room mate introduced me to the game. He was a bard named Niloiv and after many times listening to his stories about overhaste auras, mobs, and epic weapons I decided to check it out. My RL friends played a bard, a pally, a cleric, and a mage. We all were very competitive and soon we were destroying group content like pros. We decided test ourselves raiding and soon became core members of Iratus Lepus for a while. At this time my friends quit EQ for RL responsibilities and after suffering through some guild drama I decided to make my home with Dark Horizon. My best EQ raiding experiences were shared with DH members and anyone who knows anything about DH knows what I am talking about. The most skilled raid force ever to grace norrath, zero player turnover, target decimation with a 40 player raid average, and a 4 day raid scedule for starters. DH also had a reputation for some of the nicest players on the server. There was no KSing, namer stealing, or training from us. We were revered as gods of Xegony and acted like nobility. The GL and half the roster retired after SOD and DH crumbled. Now I'm kicking butt on Drinial.
